@startuml
' @id(DOM-RENDER-ENGINE)
' @ref(USE-DIFF-DIAGRAM)
'
' Objective-side domain anchor for the single deterministic render
' engine: the mdd-render crate driven by the `mdd render` mdd-cli
' subcommand. It exists so the tree-parity and path-mirror invariants
' have a domain concept to constrain. The /mdd-render skill is a thin
' wrapper that adds only interpretive judgment (fuzzy subset intake,
' diagnostic triage, fix suggestions), never mechanics.
'
' @desc(DOM-RENDER-ENGINE, "The single deterministic render engine: the mdd-render crate invoked through the `mdd render` mdd-cli subcommand. Its set of renderable trees is exactly the one mdd-core Project enumeration (models, cycle diffs, OCL constraints, whole-map, deploy, review-diff); every enumerated source file is rasterized to a rendered path that is a pure deterministic mirror of the source path. `mdd render` with no args covers the full set; --only <trees> or explicit paths render a subset. The /mdd-render skill is a thin wrapper over it.")
title Render engine — domain (objective)

class RenderEngine {
  + project : Project
  + renderedTrees : Set(Tree)
  + sources() : Set(SourceFile)
  + render(s : SourceFile) : RenderedFile
  + renderedPathOf(s : SourceFile) : Path
}

class Project {
  + enumeratedTrees : Set(Tree)
  + sourcesFor(t : Tree) : Set(SourceFile)
}

class SourceFile {
  + path : Path
  + tree : Tree
}

class RenderedFile {
  + path : Path
}

enum Tree {
  Models
  CycleDiffs
  OclConstraints
  WholeMap
  Deploy
  ReviewDiff
}

RenderEngine "1" o-- "1" Project : tree set (single source)
RenderEngine ..> SourceFile : enumerates via Project
RenderEngine ..> RenderedFile : writes mirror
SourceFile "1" --> "1" RenderedFile : deterministic mirror
Project --> Tree

note bottom of RenderEngine
  Single source of truth: renderedTrees is exactly
  Project.enumeratedTrees — no second, hand-maintained
  list in skill prose (OCL-RENDER-TREE-PARITY).
  renderedPathOf is a pure path mirror
  (OCL-RENDER-PATH-MIRROR).
end note
@enduml
